$ Windows Settings: Ease of Access

The → Windows/keyboard-shortcuts[keyboard shortcut] to open the Ease of Access center is `Windows + u`.

Ease of Access settings allow to modify vision, hearing and interaction:
table { ll
  Display ☰ 
  Mouse Pointer ☰
  Text Cursor ☰
  Magnifier ☰
  Color filters ☰
  High contrast ☰
  Narrator ☰
  Audio ☰
  Closed captions ☰
  Speech ☰
  Keyboard ☰ On screen keyboard (`→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/osk_exe`), Use sticky keys, Use toggle keys, Use filter keys, Change how keyboard shortcuts work (by underlining access keys), Print Screen shortcut.
table }


sa:

  → Windows/settings
